<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 04 at 2:39PM CDT  by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Jackson,
southwestern Kiowa and southeastern Greer Counties through 315 PM
CDT...
At 239 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles west of Olustee, moving northeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Altus, Blair, Olustee, Martha, Friendship, Altus Air Force Base and
Warren.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
